The '''''Wroshyr''''' was a saucer-shaped ship that belonged to the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Chenlambec]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. He named it after the [[Wroshyr tree/Legends|Wroshyr trees]] of his homeworld [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]].

In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]] shortly after the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], Chenlambec and his bounty hunting apprentice [[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian I'att]] boarded [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] personal [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']], as part of an elaborate plan to capture the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] hunter [[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]]. Because their true intentions were not to seek the posted [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] bounty on the passengers of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], the ''Wroshyr'' and its crew intentionally docked with the ''Executor'' too late to be scrutinized by Vader for the job, though it is uncertain if they were first cleared for the job by Vader's screening crew, who had rejected other hunters.

Chenlambec and I'att formed a partnership with Bossk to secretly lead him away from [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]]. To do so, they were forced to embark on their masquerade aboard Bossk's own ship, the [[Hound's Tooth/Legends|''Hound's Tooth'']], and to leave the ''Wroshyr'' docked in a hangar bay within the ''Executor''. To formally do so, they were required to pay Imperial docking costs by the day, but Chenlambec would never retrieve his ship. After capturing and collecting an Imperial bounty on Bossk, the two hunters took his ship as their own.

The ''Wroshyr'' was left aboard the ''Executor''.

